---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Marco and Meridian Build, an indie dev studio building digital products."
  wide
>
  <div class="about-hero">
    <div>
      <h1>About Meridian Build</h1>
      <p class="about-intro">
        One person, multiple products, constant iteration.
        Meridian Build is the name I gave this practice of designing, building, and shipping
        software products as a solo developer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>The Person</h2>
      <p>
        I'm Marco, a solo developer building digital products.
        I write code, design interfaces, handle infrastructure, do marketing,
        answer support emails, and everything else that comes with running software
        as a one-person operation.
      </p>
      <p>
        My primary stack is Ruby on Rails for backend work, with React and TypeScript
        when the project calls for it. I care about shipping working software quickly,
        writing code that's easy to change, and building things people actually use.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>The Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        Find real problems, build focused solutions, ship early, learn from users,
        and improve. No feature bloat. No enterprise sales cycles.
        No raising a round to hire 20 people before finding product-market fit.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's not a company with employees or an office. It's a solo operation:
        one person, multiple products, constant iteration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>Current Focus</h2>
      <p>
        Right now, most of my energy goes into <a href="https://outfitmaker.ai">OutfitMaker.ai</a>,
        an AI wardrobe management app that's live with paying users.
        On the side, I'm building <a href="/projects/fastpass">FastPass.email</a>,
        an escrow-based messaging platform.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>The Blog</h2>
      <p>
        I write about what I learn while building. Technical deep-dives into Rails,
        AI integration, frontend architecture. Honest numbers about growth, revenue,
        and what marketing strategies work at the indie scale.
      </p>
      <p>
        The tone is personal and direct. I write about mistakes as much as successes.
        There's enough polished marketing content in the world. I'd rather be useful
        than impressive.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
